      "content": "Surely you're not two-headed, yet here you stand, confused still; sharpen owls' beaks, but heed the writing on the wall. The sharp jabs akin to a mistaken bird pelt your throat—naught but the dojo where anxiety lays its dusty clods upon your floor. A calmed mind rather than fierce medicine we crave, yet doubter's quest—hold chin and sing plain chants of 'breath, breathe, breathe'.\n\nIn the heels of shadows, laughs hard—soothing can cure worries—or spiral. Miraculously, still it's only fear by own binding, breathing teaches patience to wind. NO leaping bellies nor strength of Kings' wrong way—quench fire with calm, surely as day. Know this: neither you nor peace return to couch 'til balance found 'midst visible breath; the circus leaves for experts steeped in healing art. For in these strange and frightened walls, wisdom sometimes dons a bellringer's cap. Do not choke life with haste—go to healers, let them chant specifically, to halve your confusion, split your fears asunder. And that, my sister, is the twisted path trod by those who let histrionics be their guide.",
